    <name>Your Reflections: Self-Regulation and EI Lesson Introduction Components </name>
    <intro>&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffff00;"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="background-color: #ffffff; color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;lease post your reflections on the&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt; following &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;question to this Discussion Forum:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="color: #800080;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img style="float: left; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px;" src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/LTA-EI-Discussionicon.jpg" alt="Discussion Graphic - multicolored heads with gear thought balloons" height="67" width="86" /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reflection Question:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt; &lt;br /&gt;How can a teacher use these six components (listed below) in a way that helps our students become self-regulated learners who:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div style="padding-left: 90px;"&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;set goals for their learning,&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;can describe their progress toward those goals, and&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;marshall their intellectual and emotional resources to solve problems and persist in working to master challenging content.&lt;em&gt; &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;EI Lesson Introduction components&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gaining students’ attention&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Informing students of the session’s objective/s&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identifying reason/s to learn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Connecting to prior knowledge&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reviewing and checking for prerequisite skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pre-teaching vocabulary&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="O1"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;strong class="O1"&gt;To enhance your learning: &lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;We encourage you to read and reply to other participants' reflections. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt;Checking back to this forum frequently (or choosing to receive e-mails for this forum) can assist in this process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="O1"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #008000;"&gt;&lt;span style="color: #000000;"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
